#if 0
----------------------------------------------------------------------
> Class:
  | Document
  $ class Document
> Purpose:
  | This class holds everything there is to know about a document.  The actual contents of the document may or may not be present at all times for memory conservation reasons.
  | The document can be told to retrieve its contents.  This is done with the _Retrieve_ call.  In case the retrieval causes a redirect, the link is followed, but this process is done only once (to prevent loops.) If the redirect didn't work, Document_not_found is returned.
> Instantiation:
  | Allocate on the heap or the stack.
> Base Classes:
  | public Object
> Important Members:
  = 1. Document ()
  = 2. Document (char*)
  = 3. Document (char*, URL&)
  = ~Document ()
  = int Length ()
  = URL& Url ()
  = DocStatus Retrieve (char*)
  = unnamed_enum DocStatus
  = URL url
  = String contents
  = int document_length
  = enum unnamed_enum {Document_ok, Document_not_found, Document_not_changed, Document_redirect}
  = No typedefs defined...
> Deriving Classes:
  | No obvious derivation is forseen
> Resource Use:
  | This class uses the Connection class to interface.
> Other Considerations:
  | OTHER
----------------------------------------------------------------------
#endif
