#if 0
----------------------------------------------------------------------
> Member Function: Document::Retrieve ;
  $ DocStatus Retrieve (char*)
> Purpose:
  | Attempt to retrieve the document specified by the URL the document already has.  This will take care of redirects returned by the server.
  | Only if the document retrieved is newer than the given date string will the document actually be retrieved.
> Calling Context:
  | 
> Return Value:
  | DocStatus
> Parameters:
  = char* date - If not NULL, specifies a date string in the format that URCs use.
> Other Considerations:
  | OTHER
